WEBVTT

00:49.549 --> 00:51.117
- Okay. Are we doing...
- Hi.

00:51.217 --> 00:52.852
- How are you?
- I'm not comin' out there.

00:52.952 --> 00:56.056
It's only a day and a half of work,
and you gonna be making $150.

00:56.156 --> 00:58.658
- I look like a damn fool.
- I'm gonna come in.

00:58.758 --> 01:01.429
Okay. One, two, thre...

01:02.028 --> 01:03.496
You better stop it.

01:03.596 --> 01:06.766
Eileen, you come in on three.
You don't say, "One, two," and come in.

01:06.866 --> 01:08.401
You say, "Three." Then you come in.

01:08.501 --> 01:13.206
Look at you. You are
dressed for success.

01:13.306 --> 01:15.308
I look like the whole
damn red-light district.

01:15.408 --> 01:17.644
I ain't had nothing like this
on since I was on that pole.

01:17.744 --> 01:21.815
Ooh. Well, just think of this as
another pole. The North Pole.

01:21.915 --> 01:23.616
They don't make it
rain at the North Pole.

01:23.716 --> 01:25.518
At my age, I can't
get no rain nowhere.

01:25.618 --> 01:27.998
I get a little drizzle,
but them quarters hurt.

01:29.856 --> 01:32.625
No, no, no. Well, this is beautiful.

01:32.725 --> 01:35.962
Just think of this as a little
extra money for you and Cora.

01:36.062 --> 01:37.764
Honey, I don't buy Cora
nothing for Christmas.

01:37.864 --> 01:39.666
I ain't bought her nothing
since she was seven years old.

01:39.766 --> 01:41.101
- You're kidding.
- That's right.

01:41.201 --> 01:44.037
Cora asked me for some money
for some dolls named Starz.

01:44.137 --> 01:45.972
I couldn't afford it.
She just wanted them Starz.

01:46.072 --> 01:48.041
So all day Christmas,
she made me feel bad.

01:48.141 --> 01:50.377
That night, Christmas dinner,
she's still sitting at the table crying.

01:50.477 --> 01:53.013
I knocked the hell out of her.
You know what happened?

01:53.113 --> 01:55.682
She saw stars. And she never
asked me for another gift.

01:55.782 --> 01:57.984
- You are dreadful. Yes, you are.
- The truth.

01:58.084 --> 02:00.820
- I can't do this, Eileen.
- Yes, you can. Stop.

02:00.920 --> 02:02.389
- Now, just smile.
- Okay. I'm smiling.

02:02.489 --> 02:04.457
Now, you should see...
Come over here.

02:04.557 --> 02:06.026
I gotta take you where you working.

02:06.126 --> 02:09.429
You should see the lovely gifts
I bought for my daughter.

02:09.529 --> 02:11.865
- How she doing?
- Oh, she is excellent.

02:11.965 --> 02:14.034
You know she went to New
York to get a degree...

02:14.134 --> 02:17.871
got her master's and up and
moved to Alabama of all places.

02:17.971 --> 02:20.573
- What the hell she move to Alabama for?
- Who knows.

02:20.673 --> 02:24.878
Anyway, she took a little job there in
some little, small school, you know.

02:24.978 --> 02:27.718
She says she wants to start a farm.

02:28.648 --> 02:32.685
- A farm? What she starting a farm for?
- I don't know. I don't know.

02:32.785 --> 02:36.222
But anyway, you know she got
tons of offers down here in Atlanta.

02:36.322 --> 02:38.958
But she didn't want to,
so what can you do?

02:39.058 --> 02:41.661
- Maybe she's trying to get away from you.
- You better stop that.

02:41.761 --> 02:43.530
- Where we going?
- My daughter loves me.

02:43.630 --> 02:47.735
Round yon Virgin Mother...

02:49.869 --> 02:52.449
- Was that you singing?
- No, ma'am.

02:52.872 --> 02:56.076
There's no one else in there,
Bailey McCoy.

02:56.176 --> 02:59.012
Come on. Walk with me.
You're late again.

02:59.112 --> 03:00.380
I'm sorry.

03:00.480 --> 03:02.715
- I'm gonna have to talk to your parents.
- No.

03:02.815 --> 03:06.319
I just woke up late.
I'll be here on time. I promise.

03:06.419 --> 03:07.887
Budget cuts, budget cuts.

03:07.987 --> 03:10.090
All right. Go on in class.

03:10.190 --> 03:12.092
- We'll talk about this later. Okay?
- Okay.

03:12.192 --> 03:14.431
And your singing.

03:17.630 --> 03:20.176
I'm not gonna come in
here and listen to this.

03:23.670 --> 03:25.511
All right, people!

03:27.340 --> 03:29.909
Now, we may have to cancel
the Christmas Jubilee this year.

03:30.009 --> 03:32.545
- No way!
- We don't have the budget!

03:32.645 --> 03:34.481
Mayor, you hold on right there.

03:34.581 --> 03:36.483
All right? Now, I grew
"poinsetters" for this.

03:36.583 --> 03:37.884
Poinsettias.

03:37.984 --> 03:39.688
- That's what I said.
- No, you didn't.

03:40.687 --> 03:42.455
If this Christmas
Jubilee don't happen...

03:42.555 --> 03:44.357
what am I gonna do with
all them "poinsetters"?

03:44.457 --> 03:46.759
- Poinsettias.
- Stop. Do I look stupid?

03:46.859 --> 03:48.761
- Tanner, I understand.
- No, sir...

03:48.861 --> 03:50.964
with all due respect,
I don't think you do.

03:51.064 --> 03:53.766
Since they built that dam upriver,
we've been barely surviving.

03:53.866 --> 03:56.069
Between that and the drought...

03:56.169 --> 03:58.104
managed to put most of
our crops out of business.

03:58.204 --> 04:00.106
We need this Christmas Jubilee
to happen. You hear me?

04:00.206 --> 04:03.143
We don't have the money.
I talked to the city council, didn't I?

04:03.243 --> 04:05.411
You did, Your Honor.
He talked to him. I heard him.

04:05.511 --> 04:08.848
- Take it out of the school.
- Hold on, Tanner McCoy.

04:08.948 --> 04:11.084
We've already cut
the school's budget...

04:11.184 --> 04:13.653
and as principal,
I have to draw the line.

04:13.753 --> 04:16.488
We have four teachers
teaching several classes.

04:16.589 --> 04:19.692
If we cut back more, we'll not be
able to finish the school year.

04:19.791 --> 04:22.562
I don't care.
Somebody has to do something.

04:22.662 --> 04:24.531
We have to have this
Christmas Jubilee.

04:24.631 --> 04:28.268
It helps too many people around here
make enough money just to stay open.

04:28.368 --> 04:30.303
We don't have the budget!

04:30.403 --> 04:34.144
When we elected you as mayor,
you said you would help us!

04:35.375 --> 04:37.977
I know. I'm sorry.

04:38.077 --> 04:41.981
Folks around here don't take too kindly
to politicians not keeping their word.

04:42.081 --> 04:45.958
You keep putting all these good people
against the wall and see what happens.

04:47.220 --> 04:49.189
Come on, fellas. Geez.

04:49.289 --> 04:51.369
- This is ridiculous.
- Absolutely.

04:56.162 --> 04:58.242
- You believe that guy?
- That was unpleasant.

04:58.731 --> 05:00.266
Yes, it was.

05:00.366 --> 05:02.068
- This is where you'll be working.
- Okay.

05:02.168 --> 05:04.003
Okay? Have you ever
done sales before?

05:04.103 --> 05:07.874
- Yes, I sold trees.
- Christmas trees?

05:07.974 --> 05:09.943
When you smoke 'em, they make
you feel like it's Christmas.

05:10.043 --> 05:12.011
If you don't stop that nasty talk.

05:12.111 --> 05:14.180
Stop it. I mean,
where goods were exchanged.

05:14.280 --> 05:16.282
I was exchanging my
goodies back in the day.

05:16.382 --> 05:17.817
Yes, indeed.

05:17.917 --> 05:19.997
- I got to bring...
- On the black market.

05:21.554 --> 05:24.624
- I got to bring you back to church.
- You ain't bringing me to no church.

05:24.724 --> 05:27.060
I ain't goin' to no church.
The devil is a lie.

05:27.160 --> 05:29.195
- And you still married to him.
- Honey, honey...

05:29.295 --> 05:31.264
- Speak of the devil, listen. Listen.
- What, what, what?

05:31.364 --> 05:33.499
- Y'all want me to work the register?
- No, no.

05:33.599 --> 05:35.068
- Other people take...
- You sure?

05:35.168 --> 05:36.970
You have to be bonded for that job.

05:37.070 --> 05:38.972
If I took the register,
I'd be bonded out.

05:39.072 --> 05:40.840
Okay. Yeah. No, no, no, no.

05:40.940 --> 05:44.744
Listen, let's go over a little quick
review of what you're supposed to do.

05:44.844 --> 05:47.647
- You teach me.
- You're supposed to direct the customers...

05:47.747 --> 05:50.583
when they ask you for something,
and you can refer to this.

05:50.683 --> 05:52.852
Okay? Now,
kitchenware is on the fifth floor.

05:52.952 --> 05:54.420
- Kitchenware, fifth floor.
- Yes.

05:54.520 --> 05:56.422
- Women's apparel is on the second...
- Y'all sell pears?

05:56.522 --> 05:58.391
Y'all got produce up there?

05:58.491 --> 06:00.994
- Clothing. Women's clothing.
- Say, "Clothing." Don't say, "A pears."

06:01.094 --> 06:02.829
I don't know what
"apparels" is. "A pears."

06:02.929 --> 06:05.131
Okay. Young adults
is on the third floor.

06:05.231 --> 06:09.002
- Young adults on the third floor.
- Makeup and perfume is here.

06:09.102 --> 06:10.603
And over there across the hall.

06:10.703 --> 06:12.939
- I get it. I'll be fine.
- All right, and listen.

06:13.039 --> 06:15.775
Most important,
everybody gets the same greeting.

06:15.875 --> 06:18.044
When they come in,
you look them in the face...

06:18.144 --> 06:21.881
you smile pretty and you say,
"Merry Christmas.

06:21.981 --> 06:24.250
It's a beautiful day at Tifton's.

06:24.350 --> 06:27.754
Joy to you and yours.
Yes, may I help you?"

06:27.854 --> 06:29.656
That what I say?
Fine. I will say that.

06:29.756 --> 06:32.025
- You wanna go over it once?
- All right.

06:32.125 --> 06:34.927
- Here's a customer. Okay.
- Can you help me?

06:35.027 --> 06:36.663
- Yes. Merry...
- Yes.

06:36.763 --> 06:38.331
Mary had a little...

06:38.431 --> 06:40.400
- No, Merry Christmas.
- Merry Christmas.

06:40.500 --> 06:43.569
- It's a beautiful day at Tip...
- Tifton's.

06:43.669 --> 06:45.905
- Tap... Tip... Tiptoes.
- Joy to you.

06:46.005 --> 06:48.608
Joy to the world and the Lord
is come, and happy Easter.

06:48.708 --> 06:51.177
What can... What can I
do for you at Tifton's?

06:51.277 --> 06:53.357
Thank you. I'm looking
for women's lingerie.

06:54.046 --> 06:56.582
Honey? Who the lingerie for?

06:56.682 --> 06:58.420
For me, of course.

06:59.419 --> 07:01.788
I don't know about you
wearing the lingeries.

07:01.888 --> 07:05.291
Those days are over, honey.
Somebody should've told you it's passed.

07:05.391 --> 07:08.161
The lingeries is for young
people with tight, firm stuff.

07:08.261 --> 07:10.630
What I would suggest you do, hunty...

07:10.730 --> 07:13.499
I would suggest you walk
across the street to Target...

07:13.599 --> 07:18.237
and ask them for some of those
really nice big, big-girl drawers...

07:18.337 --> 07:20.239
so that you will be comfortable.

07:20.339 --> 07:22.275
You don't wanna walk around
with a slingshot up your butt.

07:22.375 --> 07:23.876
- Eileen!
- Come, come, come.

07:23.976 --> 07:25.445
Come. Let me help you.

07:25.545 --> 07:27.347
- You are so rude!
- She's something.

07:27.447 --> 07:31.484
No, you are the one that's rude
anytime you bring lingerie to a man.

07:31.584 --> 07:34.587
Who was the 37th president
of the United States?

07:34.687 --> 07:36.266
I know.

07:40.059 --> 07:41.638
Bailey, do you know?

07:44.263 --> 07:45.732
I know the answer.

07:45.832 --> 07:48.901
I didn't ask you. I asked Bailey.

07:49.001 --> 07:52.271
He don't know. He's always dirty.

07:52.371 --> 07:54.807
And he's just a farm boy.

07:54.907 --> 08:00.246
Yes, but he's the only one to get
an A on all three of his last tests.

08:00.346 --> 08:02.648
What did you get, Lucy?

08:02.748 --> 08:04.250
Or you, Larry?

08:04.350 --> 08:06.760
There will be no
bullying in this class.

08:08.488 --> 08:10.757
I'll see you all tomorrow.
Do your homework.

08:10.857 --> 08:13.359
Look over the list of songs
for the Christmas Jubilee.

08:13.459 --> 08:16.362
Christmas is five days away.

08:16.462 --> 08:18.508
Hold on a second, Bailey.

08:24.637 --> 08:27.774
You gotta start speaking up
and participating in class.

08:27.874 --> 08:29.609
I know you knew the answer.

08:29.709 --> 08:32.010
You're are so smart and talented.

08:32.111 --> 08:36.215
You get an A on every test.
You gotta believe in yourself.

08:36.315 --> 08:39.885
Lucy's right.
I'm just an old farm boy.

08:41.153 --> 08:43.655
There is no such thing
as "just a farm boy."

08:43.756 --> 08:47.065
You are smart. You can
be anything you want.

08:48.494 --> 08:51.731
I can only imagine if you could
just stay awake in class.

08:51.831 --> 08:54.467
- Are you up late at night?
- No, ma'am.

08:54.567 --> 08:58.205
I want you to sing the lead
solo at the Christmas Jubilee.

08:59.171 --> 09:01.073
I'm sorry. I can't do that.

09:01.173 --> 09:03.583
- Yes, you can.
- No.

09:05.344 --> 09:07.651
You know what? I really
gotta go, Miss Williams.

09:09.215 --> 09:11.591
My daddy's gonna be
waiting for me at home.

09:12.852 --> 09:14.090
Go on.

09:25.197 --> 09:26.332
Hello?

09:26.432 --> 09:28.434
I don't hear from you in six years...

09:28.534 --> 09:31.804
and you call me out of the
blue because you need my help.

09:31.904 --> 09:33.473
Don't blame that on me.

09:33.573 --> 09:36.409
You're the one who married Kelly
and stopped returning my calls.

09:36.509 --> 09:38.177
You're not still bitter, are you?

09:38.277 --> 09:40.789
Maybe. How is she?

09:41.781 --> 09:44.555
I don't know. We're divorced.

09:45.651 --> 09:47.386
Good. She was such a tramp.

09:47.486 --> 09:51.023
I can't believe you married her and
dumped me. That's what you get.

09:51.123 --> 09:53.192
Okay, okay.

09:53.292 --> 09:56.128
Hey, pull up, It was high school.
Am I forgiven?

09:56.228 --> 09:59.765
That depends. Can you help
me with my school situation?

09:59.865 --> 10:02.702
- So you need sponsorship?
- Yes.

10:02.802 --> 10:04.770
A call came in just as I
was leaving a meeting..

10:04.870 --> 10:07.607
With a company that's in
the middle of a PR nightmare.

10:07.707 --> 10:09.942
They could use some
goodwill right now.

10:10.042 --> 10:13.779
Actually, in a town like yours.
So your timing may be perfect.

10:13.879 --> 10:15.515
Tell me about it.

10:15.615 --> 10:18.451
Can't do that until
we have a contract.

10:18.551 --> 10:22.221
- You don't trust me?
- No, no, no, it's not that.

10:22.321 --> 10:24.526
I have to protect my
interests, that's all.

10:25.958 --> 10:27.260
Tell you what.

10:27.360 --> 10:29.595
I'll come down with a contract,
you get your people to sign...

10:29.695 --> 10:31.364
and I'm sure I can pull in...

10:31.464 --> 10:34.408
at least a hundred grand for
your school and its event.

10:35.101 --> 10:37.904
$100,000. That would be great.

10:38.004 --> 10:39.906
How soon can you get here?

10:40.006 --> 10:41.774
You need the money
right away, don't you?

10:41.874 --> 10:44.577
Yeah. So you're willing
to drive down to Alabama?

10:44.677 --> 10:47.113
I will drive over tomorrow.

10:47.213 --> 10:49.615
We'll get the contract signed,
then I'll have to leave...

10:49.715 --> 10:52.552
but I'll be back for the event.

10:52.652 --> 10:54.732
That would be fantastic.

10:55.688 --> 10:58.057
Oliver, thank you so much.

10:58.157 --> 10:59.292
See you soon.

10:59.392 --> 11:00.493
- You got it.
- Bye.

11:00.593 --> 11:02.866
Child, that Powerball is going up.

11:05.965 --> 11:09.168
Hello? Hey, I need y'all to
go get me some scratch-offs.

11:09.268 --> 11:11.170
- Yeah, and play the numbers for me.
- Can you help me?

11:11.270 --> 11:12.772
That Powerball has
gotten really high.

11:12.872 --> 11:14.173
Play number 22...

11:14.273 --> 11:16.242
- Excuse me.
- 17,5 and 6.

11:16.342 --> 11:19.145
Go play them numbers, and bring
me a bunch of scratch offs. Yeah.

11:19.245 --> 11:21.714
Just two, three of 'em.
Don't spend a lot of money.

11:21.814 --> 11:23.049
I need some help!

11:23.149 --> 11:24.951
Hold on, 'cause somebody's
screaming at me.

11:25.051 --> 11:27.131
I'm getting ready to
choke her. Hold on.

11:29.488 --> 11:32.158
Lady, you gonna need a damn
doctor if you holler at me again.

11:32.258 --> 11:35.027
Do you understand?
Now, what can I help you with?

11:35.127 --> 11:37.029
- I need a watch for my husband.
- A men's watch.

11:37.129 --> 11:40.266
A men's watch. You know,
I like it with a leather band.

11:40.366 --> 11:42.768
- You know, a nice thin watch.
- Here are some men's...

11:42.868 --> 11:44.971
Oh, hell. It's time for my break.

11:45.071 --> 11:46.906
- Time for my break.
- Break?

11:47.006 --> 11:48.474
No, wait.

11:48.574 --> 11:50.042
- You're so rude.
- Bye, bye, bye.

11:50.142 --> 11:52.878
- You rude as hell. You rude as hell.
- Please. I need a watch.

11:52.978 --> 11:55.348
Get out of my way. I'm trying
to go to the break room.

11:55.448 --> 11:56.526
Wait! Come back!

12:00.886 --> 12:02.465
You still here?

12:03.255 --> 12:05.024
He called me back.

12:05.124 --> 12:07.204
Yeah? And?

12:08.127 --> 12:12.832
He thinks he can get us
$100,000 in sponsorship money.

12:12.932 --> 12:14.767
$100,000?

12:14.867 --> 12:17.103
- Oh, my goodness, that would be so great.
- I know.

12:17.203 --> 12:19.438
That would not only
pay for the Jubilee...

12:19.538 --> 12:22.241
that would take us well into
next year's school year.

12:22.341 --> 12:24.677
We could get new books,
maybe even a new computer.

12:24.777 --> 12:27.580
Wait, calm down. It hasn't
happened yet. It's not done.

12:27.680 --> 12:30.349
Okay, but I have faith that it is.

12:30.449 --> 12:34.820
Lacey, thank you so much for
doing this. I really appreciate it.

12:34.920 --> 12:38.324
I know this school is not the best,
but it is all we got.

12:38.424 --> 12:40.860
And I know you could have gone
anywhere in the country...

12:40.960 --> 12:43.029
with the credentials you have.

12:43.129 --> 12:45.505
- I love it here.
- Thank you.

12:46.899 --> 12:48.968
He's coming down tomorrow
with the contract.

12:49.068 --> 12:51.937
This is so wonderful!
I gotta call the mayor.

12:52.037 --> 12:54.073
- Yes.
- He's gonna be so excited.

12:54.173 --> 12:56.275
This is going to be a wonderful
Christmas after all!

12:56.375 --> 12:57.954
It's gonna be fantastic.

13:00.212 --> 13:01.950
All right. I'll see you tomorrow.

13:27.907 --> 13:30.643
- Hello?
- I must be dialing the wrong number.

13:30.743 --> 13:33.713
You said that already,
but you called back five times.

13:33.813 --> 13:35.548
So what number you trying to get?

13:35.648 --> 13:37.983
I'm trying to reach
my daughter, Lacey.

13:38.083 --> 13:40.386
Oh, yeah. Yeah,
she just walked in. Hold on.

13:40.486 --> 13:42.566
- Who is that?
- Your mama.

13:48.427 --> 13:50.262
- Hi, Mama.
- Who was that?

13:50.362 --> 13:51.864
That was Conner.

13:51.964 --> 13:53.543
Conner?

13:54.300 --> 13:56.936
That's the guy you hired
to help you with the farm?

13:57.036 --> 13:58.738
Yeah, that's him.

13:58.838 --> 14:01.574
Okay. I don't know if I
like him up there with you.

14:01.674 --> 14:03.142
Suppose he gets fresh...

14:03.242 --> 14:05.544
and you don't have no man
up there to protect you.

14:05.644 --> 14:07.747
Mama, I'm fine. What's going on?

14:07.847 --> 14:10.282
I can't wait until you
taste the dinner...

14:10.382 --> 14:12.585
I have prepared for
you for Christmas.

14:12.685 --> 14:15.187
Yeah, I've been meaning
to talk to you about that.

14:15.287 --> 14:17.697
I'm not gonna be able
to come home this year.

14:18.190 --> 14:19.658
What?

14:19.758 --> 14:21.761
Uh-uh. It's Christmas.

14:21.861 --> 14:24.630
I know, it's just I'm just
getting settled in...

14:24.730 --> 14:26.799
and the farm needs a lot of work.

14:26.899 --> 14:29.301
Uh-uh. You not no
farmer in the dell now.

14:29.401 --> 14:30.870
It's not just the farm.

14:30.970 --> 14:33.172
They've also decided to
extended the school year...

14:33.272 --> 14:34.740
to the day before Christmas.

14:34.840 --> 14:37.610
- What kind of school is that?
- We lost a lot of days...

14:37.710 --> 14:40.746
because of the storms this summer,
so we have to make them up,

14:40.846 --> 14:43.115
And I'm helping the kids prepare
songs for the Christmas Jubilee.

14:43.215 --> 14:47.086
And we have a budget crisis.
So it's just too busy right now, Mom.

14:47.186 --> 14:48.087
I'll come up there.

14:48.187 --> 14:49.588
- No.
- Yes.

14:49.688 --> 14:51.657
- I haven't seen you in nine months...
- It's not the right time.

14:51.757 --> 14:53.659
And you don't drive.

14:53.759 --> 14:56.262
I can get somebody to
drive up there with me.

14:56.362 --> 14:58.631
I can ask your Aunt
Madea to come with me.

14:58.731 --> 15:01.901
Mama, can we just skip it this year?
It's only Christmas.

15:02.001 --> 15:03.469
You bite your tongue,

15:03.569 --> 15:05.838
Christmas is the time of year...

15:05.938 --> 15:10.282
when we celebrate the birth of
Jesus with our families and...

15:12.645 --> 15:14.613
Lacey, I don't have
to tell you that...

15:14.713 --> 15:17.416
you and I are the
only family we have,

15:17.516 --> 15:19.596
I know. Mom, are you crying?

15:21.954 --> 15:23.556
What was that, Conner?

15:24.323 --> 15:25.758
I didn't say anything.

15:25.858 --> 15:28.494
I'm sorry. Conner needs
my help, Mama. I gotta go.

15:28.594 --> 15:30.765
I'll talk to you tomorrow.
Love you Bye,

15:34.934 --> 15:37.903
Do not look at me like that.
You don't understand.

15:38.003 --> 15:39.878
I didn't say a word.

15:45.778 --> 15:47.279
Are you okay?

15:47.379 --> 15:51.417
Girl, I don't know why I let you talk
me into comin' and doin' this job.

15:51.517 --> 15:54.453
- I didn't take my medicine this morning.
- What medicine?

15:54.553 --> 15:56.758
Five milligrams
of "Don't choke that ho."

15:57.790 --> 15:59.692
These customers gettin' right...

15:59.792 --> 16:01.827
I feel I'm getting ready
to maybe catch a case.

16:01.927 --> 16:04.473
- I could spit.
- What's wrong with you?

16:04.897 --> 16:07.238
Lacey's not coming for Christmas.

16:07.967 --> 16:09.602
That ain't no problem.
Children grow up.

16:09.702 --> 16:11.570
They don't wanna come home sometimes.

16:11.670 --> 16:13.249
Something's wrong.

16:14.340 --> 16:15.474
- Eileen?
- What?

16:15.574 --> 16:18.678
I know that look in your eye.
Don't go jumpin' to no conclusion.

16:19.345 --> 16:21.513
I don't jump to conclusions.

16:21.613 --> 16:24.516
Last time you went to
the doctor, you had a rash.

16:24.616 --> 16:27.820
Walked up in there, told the man
you had cancer and you was dying.

16:27.920 --> 16:32.658
Madea, many people in my
family have died of cancer.

16:32.758 --> 16:34.693
- I know your family.
- Yes.

16:34.793 --> 16:37.162
- My grandmother.
- Got hit by a bus.

16:37.262 --> 16:41.267
But she had cancer. My uncle Bayrod.

16:41.367 --> 16:44.003
- Drowned.
- Because he had cancer.

16:44.103 --> 16:45.804
- Eileen?
- What?

16:45.904 --> 16:48.107
No, no, no, no. Something is wrong.

16:48.207 --> 16:50.843
Something is wrong with my child,
and I'm gonna find out what it is.

16:50.943 --> 16:53.779
She's down there in the country,
and I don't know what's going on.

16:53.879 --> 16:56.382
I haven't seen where she works,
where she live.

16:56.482 --> 16:58.951
- It's just awful!
- Your daughter is grown.

16:59.051 --> 17:01.954
Leave her alone. If she want to
come home, she will come home.

17:02.054 --> 17:03.633
What you planning on doing?

17:04.223 --> 17:05.691
I'm gonna go down there.

17:05.790 --> 17:08.193
I'd like to see that,
'cause you don't drive.

17:08.292 --> 17:11.262
- You do.
- Child, I ain't goin' to no Alabama.

17:11.363 --> 17:14.934
Last time I was in Alabama, I was chained
to Andy Young and Jesse Jackson.

17:15.034 --> 17:18.273
- You marched?
- We wasn't upright when we was marching.

17:20.305 --> 17:23.008
- We gonna go down there.
- I'm not driving to no Alabama.

17:23.108 --> 17:26.011
All my stuff is illegal. I don't
like driving through Georgia.

17:26.111 --> 17:28.314
You think I'm gettin' ready
to drive through Alabama?

17:28.414 --> 17:30.382
- I'll pay you.
- What time you wanna leave?

17:30.482 --> 17:32.484
Okay. Good.

17:32.584 --> 17:34.553
No, child. I can't get on
the road with my Cadillac.

17:34.653 --> 17:38.791
It's got 4,785,000 miles on it,
and I just changed the oil in it.

17:38.891 --> 17:40.859
Every light on the dashboard say...

17:40.959 --> 17:43.266
"You crazy as hell if
you go anywhere in me."

17:44.763 --> 17:48.000
- Madea...
- I can't do it, hon. I'm sorry.

17:48.100 --> 17:51.181
Have you ever thought maybe she
just don't want to see you, Eileen?

17:52.171 --> 17:54.006
My daughter loves me.

17:54.106 --> 17:57.009
She loves spending time with me.

17:57.109 --> 18:00.412
All right, honey. If you find a ride,
I'll go up there with you.

18:00.512 --> 18:03.024
All right. Well, I will work on it.

18:15.494 --> 18:17.005
Conner.

18:17.896 --> 18:20.632
- What the hell you think you're doin'?
- What are you talking about?

18:20.732 --> 18:22.534
I was down at the feed store.

18:22.634 --> 18:24.670
They tell me you're planning
on planting corn this year.

18:24.770 --> 18:26.305
Yeah, I was.

18:26.405 --> 18:28.540
I plant corn.

18:28.640 --> 18:31.310
Well, actually, what I'm
working on can help all of us.

18:31.410 --> 18:33.479
- What you're working on?
- Yeah.

18:33.579 --> 18:37.016
You think you learned something down
in that college that I don't know about?

18:37.116 --> 18:39.856
- That's not what I meant, Tanner.
- No, you don't.

18:40.786 --> 18:43.389
And you better find
something else to plant.

18:43.489 --> 18:46.158
You been gone from around
here for far too long.

18:46.258 --> 18:47.826
I mean it, Conner.

18:47.926 --> 18:51.667
Otherwise, I'll be here every day,
kick your ass like I did back in school.

19:00.506 --> 19:03.575
Eileen, we've had a lot of
complaints about your friend.

19:03.675 --> 19:05.144
Oh, no.

19:05.244 --> 19:07.279
Hey there. I was
getting ready to go...

19:07.379 --> 19:10.249
- What's the matter?
- We're going to have to ask you to leave.

19:10.349 --> 19:14.153
Good, it's about damn time.
I get out of... Give me my check.

19:14.253 --> 19:15.661
We'll mail it to you.

19:16.989 --> 19:19.024
No, honey. Eileen,
you better tell her.

19:19.124 --> 19:21.960
Ain't nobody gonna mail me no check.
I didn't mail my work up in here.

19:22.060 --> 19:24.329
You ain't mailing me no check.
Where's my money?

19:24.429 --> 19:27.099
Madea, go home. I'll call you later.

19:27.199 --> 19:29.568
I don't give a damn who calling who.
Somebody gonna give me my money.

19:29.668 --> 19:31.770
Would you please leave quietly?

19:31.870 --> 19:33.972
Oh, sure. You want
me to leave quietly?

19:34.072 --> 19:35.808
You want me to leave quietly?

19:35.908 --> 19:38.077
I will show you how
to leave damn quietly.

19:38.177 --> 19:40.045
Y'all gonna give me my damn money.

19:40.145 --> 19:44.049
But before I get my damn purse,
I'm gonna get money out this register.

19:44.149 --> 19:45.851
- Excuse me.
- No, no.

19:45.951 --> 19:48.754
No, you can't do that. Put... Madea.

19:48.854 --> 19:50.756
Where my purse?
Unlock the damn thing!

19:50.856 --> 19:53.692
I got my purse here. This is $150.

19:53.792 --> 19:56.495
- This is what you owe me.
- Put that money back.

19:56.595 --> 19:58.564
I'm gonna take something else.
I'm gonna take this dress.

19:58.664 --> 20:00.632
- Stop it!
- Take whatever I want out of here.

20:00.732 --> 20:02.734
What's this pulling on me?

20:02.834 --> 20:04.470
You're embarrassing us.

20:04.570 --> 20:07.473
What the hell y'all looking at?
What the hell all y'all looking at?

20:07.573 --> 20:10.843
It's Christmas, and I'm takin'
what the hell I want up in here!

20:10.943 --> 20:14.379
What y'all gonna do about it?
What y'all gonna do about it?

20:14.479 --> 20:17.015
- I'll take this too.
- She didn't take her medication today.

20:17.115 --> 20:19.985
You got me coming up here,
trying to work in this place...

20:20.085 --> 20:21.787
and I don't know
what the hell gonna...

20:21.887 --> 20:23.956
Get out the way!
What the hell goin' on?

20:24.056 --> 20:27.359
- I know what the hell I'm doing!
- She has never acted like this before.

20:27.459 --> 20:29.495
I'm fabulous. I'm gone
with the wind fabulous.

20:29.595 --> 20:31.333
I am so sorry.

20:50.015 --> 20:53.619
Hi. I'm Lacey Williams,
Bailey's teacher.

20:53.719 --> 20:56.561
- Right. Come on in.
- Thank you.

21:00.525 --> 21:02.327
- How are you?
- I'm fine.

21:02.427 --> 21:04.663
I just stopped by to talk to you.

21:04.763 --> 21:07.833
I graded another one of Bailey's
homework assignments...

21:07.933 --> 21:09.234
Listen, I'm sorry.

21:09.334 --> 21:12.571
He has to help his daddy at night,
so he doesn't get much time to study.

21:12.671 --> 21:15.841
Then he gets up early in the
morning to work with him...

21:15.941 --> 21:18.920
so I'll just have to get
on him to do better.

21:19.978 --> 21:21.819
He can't get any better.

21:22.314 --> 21:24.850
- He gets straight A's.
- What?

21:24.950 --> 21:28.520
Yeah. And to know he works after
school and in the morning...

21:28.620 --> 21:30.455
is even more impressive.

21:30.555 --> 21:34.262
He really should go to a gifted
school with a fine arts department.

21:35.894 --> 21:37.302
Wow.

21:39.331 --> 21:42.401
I always knew he was smart.
I didn't know he was that smart.

21:42.501 --> 21:45.971
Me and his daddy never
got much schoolin'.

21:46.071 --> 21:49.508
You really think Bailey could
make it outside of this place?

21:49.608 --> 21:51.381
I know he can.

21:52.311 --> 21:54.646
I mean, that's really
all I want for him.

21:54.746 --> 21:57.549
Bailey is always telling me
how good you are to him...

21:57.649 --> 22:01.220
and that you defend him in front
of those other kids, so thank you.

22:01.320 --> 22:04.756
- Well, he's a very special boy.
- Yeah, he is.

22:04.856 --> 22:06.658
- Have a seat.
- Sure. Thank you.

22:06.758 --> 22:09.270
- Can I get you something to drink?
- Yes.

22:09.861 --> 22:11.440
Thanks.

22:15.300 --> 22:16.879
Thank you.

22:18.270 --> 22:22.507
He also told me you want him to
sing at the Christmas Jubilee?

22:22.607 --> 22:24.943
Yes. He has a beautiful voice.

22:25.043 --> 22:27.679
You think the Jubilee is
gonna happen this year?

22:27.779 --> 22:29.248
Yes, haven't you heard?

22:29.348 --> 22:31.917
I got a friend of mine to
get us a sponsorship for it.

22:32.017 --> 22:33.919
So it's definitely gonna happen.

22:34.019 --> 22:36.793
- That's great news.
- Yeah, it really is.

22:41.560 --> 22:44.029
Oh, hell. What do you want?

22:44.129 --> 22:47.267
- Hi, I'm Lacey Williams.
- I know who you are.

22:47.866 --> 22:50.636
You're Bailey's teacher.
Bailey's gonna be late to school.

22:50.736 --> 22:53.908
He's got a lot of work to do here,
that's if he makes it at all.

22:54.573 --> 22:57.051
No need come around
here no more. Okay?

22:58.410 --> 23:00.217
I am so sorry.

23:02.848 --> 23:04.427
Merry Christmas.

23:09.521 --> 23:11.523
Oliver, this is so funny.

23:11.623 --> 23:14.960
I hadn't spoken to your mother
in a while, and we got talking...

23:15.060 --> 23:18.163
and she said you were drivin'
to Alabama to see Lacey!

23:18.263 --> 23:20.499
Miss Eileen, I'm happy
to have the company.

23:20.599 --> 23:23.935
Did I tell you I take blood pressure
medicine that makes me have to pee?

23:24.035 --> 23:27.172
- I'll have to go to the bathroom soon.
- Okay, go in the bush.

23:27.272 --> 23:30.444
I'm not putting my tush over no bush.
I don't know what's wrong with you.

23:32.844 --> 23:35.049
The leaves fell off
of it, but it work!

23:35.547 --> 23:37.449
- Jesus. Baby...
- It the wintertime.

23:37.549 --> 23:39.651
Just keep your eyes ahead.

23:39.751 --> 23:42.821
Okay? No, no, no. She's always
like this, since a child.

23:42.921 --> 23:44.389
- Yeah, since my childhood.
- Something's wrong.

23:44.489 --> 23:45.957
Something's wrong, but we accept it.

23:46.057 --> 23:48.026
You sure you didn't tell
her we were coming?

23:48.126 --> 23:50.162
I wanted this to be a big surprise!

23:50.262 --> 23:51.841
I'm sure.

23:52.264 --> 23:55.967
'Cause she's gonna be
so happy to see you!

23:56.067 --> 24:00.172
Madea, I told him how much
Lacey talks about him.

24:00.272 --> 24:03.508
Why you hollerin' like I'm in the back
of an airplane and you in first class?

24:03.608 --> 24:06.111
I can hear you. You right here.

24:06.211 --> 24:08.080
All I'm saying is this...

24:08.180 --> 24:10.082
- What's your name, boy? Olive Oil?
- Oliver.

24:10.182 --> 24:11.650
All I'm saying is this.

24:11.750 --> 24:14.853
If she wanted to talk to you,
she would have called you all the time.

24:14.953 --> 24:16.555
Don't get your hopes
up listening to Eileen.

24:16.655 --> 24:19.858
Don't listen to her. You two
are gonna be together again.

24:19.958 --> 24:22.260
You'd like that, wouldn't you?
I see it on your face.

24:22.360 --> 24:23.995
I see it on your face. Yeah!

24:24.095 --> 24:25.997
I would like to see us
have another chance.

24:26.097 --> 24:28.700
Y'all was in high school back then.
I got to pee, son.

24:28.800 --> 24:31.203
You been driving around
in circles for way too long.

24:31.303 --> 24:34.339
Go on over there. Pull over there,
ask these people directions.

24:34.439 --> 24:36.708
I'm gonna go in here
and use the bathroom.

24:36.808 --> 24:38.610
No, Madea.
This place don't look right.

24:38.710 --> 24:40.946
Eileen, here. This a...
Child, please.

24:41.046 --> 24:43.615
I grew up in the country.
Ain't nobody in here.

24:43.715 --> 24:45.795
He what sittin'
there willy-whilin'. Ask him.

24:46.485 --> 24:49.087
Lord, this thing is high.
You gotta get me a step.

24:49.187 --> 24:51.323
'Scuse me, sir.
You look like a nice man.

24:51.423 --> 24:53.592
How you doin'? We are lost.
He trying to find direction.

24:53.692 --> 24:55.727
I need a bathroom. Is there
a bathroom here somewhere?

24:55.827 --> 24:58.029
Yes, ma'am. Right over yonder.

24:58.129 --> 25:01.073
Get the directions here.
I got me to pee.

25:05.036 --> 25:06.638
Got to pee. Hell...

25:08.874 --> 25:10.112
What the...

25:19.851 --> 25:22.487
Go! Drive! Drive, Olive Oil, drive!

25:22.587 --> 25:24.956
Put the pedal to the metal.
Get the hell outta here!

25:25.056 --> 25:27.526
- They're tryin' to get me!
- What did you do?

25:27.626 --> 25:30.036
Drive! Hell, they're KKK!

25:38.570 --> 25:40.806
- This ain't the right address, is it?
- That's what she said.

25:40.906 --> 25:45.143
This can't be the right address.
These people might not be friendly.

25:45.243 --> 25:49.848
Look, this is 2013,
and it's almost Christmas.

25:49.948 --> 25:51.583
Sure it'll be fine.

25:51.683 --> 25:54.119
Boy, did you see what I
just went through in town?

25:54.219 --> 25:55.687
True.

25:55.787 --> 25:58.089
This just don't feel right.

25:58.189 --> 26:01.993
Up here in these woods,
ain't nobody around but us and trees.

26:02.093 --> 26:04.173
I don't like this.
Go knock on the door.

26:05.764 --> 26:08.467
- Thanks a lot.
- What you worried about, son?

26:08.567 --> 26:10.535
Somebody got to
live to tell the story.

26:10.635 --> 26:13.071
Tell 'em what happened to you.
Somebody got be an activist.

26:13.171 --> 26:15.173
Somebody got to call Sharpton.

26:15.273 --> 26:16.681
Never mind.

26:20.360 --> 26:22.362
Conner, where are you going?

26:22.462 --> 26:25.198
- Hey, what's going on?
- I mentioned Tanner and he lost it.

26:25.298 --> 26:27.768
- Conner!
- I've been waiting to see this.

26:27.868 --> 26:29.870
- I'm goin' with you, boy.
- Conner!

26:36.670 --> 26:38.004
Conner!

26:44.913 --> 26:48.050
- Uh-oh. Who is that?
- I told you this was the wrong address.

26:48.150 --> 26:49.923
We gotta go. Back up.

26:52.320 --> 26:53.955
There she is! Pull up.

26:54.055 --> 26:55.590
We're at the right place.

26:55.690 --> 26:57.599
- Come on. Hurry up.
- There she is.

26:59.528 --> 27:02.336
- Lacey!
- Look at you.

27:05.000 --> 27:07.444
Oh, my word. What are you doing here?

27:10.071 --> 27:13.742
I hitched a ride
with Oliver. Surprise!

27:13.842 --> 27:15.310
Surprise!

27:15.410 --> 27:17.679
- We came.
- Surprise.

27:17.779 --> 27:19.358
Who are you?

27:20.782 --> 27:22.751
I'm Conner.

27:22.851 --> 27:25.192
Girl, what the coroner doing here?
Who done died?

27:28.089 --> 27:32.433
You are the farmhand that
she hired. Yes, yes, yes, yes.

27:33.495 --> 27:35.097
I am Eileen, her mother.

27:35.197 --> 27:39.507
And this is Madea,
her great-aunt on my daddy's side.

27:41.269 --> 27:43.171
She sure don't look happy to see us.

27:43.271 --> 27:45.373
You better bite your tongue.

27:45.473 --> 27:48.486
She is happy to see
me anytime. Tell her.

27:51.479 --> 27:55.550
That don't look like happiness, honey.
That look like puredee constipation.

27:56.151 --> 27:57.619
Hi, Conner.

27:57.719 --> 27:59.087
How are ya? How ya doing?

27:59.187 --> 28:01.089
This handsome thing...

28:01.189 --> 28:03.859
this is Oliver, her boyfriend.

28:03.959 --> 28:05.694
Her boyfriend?

28:05.794 --> 28:07.931
Ex-boyfriend.

28:08.864 --> 28:11.566
It was nice of you to call him.

28:11.666 --> 28:14.269
That was a nice ruse to
get to see him. Fund-raiser.

28:14.369 --> 28:16.338
No, it wasn't a ruse.

28:16.438 --> 28:18.240
You know you miss him.

28:18.340 --> 28:21.209
Anyway, could you get my bags,
farmhand, please?

28:21.309 --> 28:23.446
- Yeah.
- I'll help.

28:24.479 --> 28:27.215
Lacey, come show us this farm.

28:27.315 --> 28:29.417
A little dusty, dusty.

28:29.517 --> 28:32.621
Come, my dear. I knew that.

28:32.721 --> 28:35.323
Baby, you know you got asthma.

28:35.423 --> 28:37.325
Mama, I don't have asthma anymore.

28:37.425 --> 28:39.628
Yeah, but you still
gotta be careful...

28:39.728 --> 28:42.364
because that could lead to cancer.

28:42.464 --> 28:44.933
Everything don't lead to cancer,
Eileen. Lord, help her.

28:45.033 --> 28:47.435
I'm gonna open the door.
Y'all need fresh air up in here.

28:47.535 --> 28:49.971
Got all these animals. This is
a nice room. I'll stay in here.

28:50.071 --> 28:51.439
- Good, good, good.
- Sure.

28:51.539 --> 28:53.975
Lacey, you do not
have a Christmas tree?

28:54.075 --> 28:55.544
- No, I don't.
- Oh, my God.

28:55.644 --> 28:58.647
- That's why you wanted me to come here.
- Yeah, that's exactly why.

28:58.747 --> 29:00.382
- I'm gonna take this room.
- Okay.

29:00.482 --> 29:01.817
- Okay?
- That's nice too.

29:01.917 --> 29:03.518
- That's a nice room.
- Thank you.

29:03.618 --> 29:06.521
- Is this one yours, Madea?
- Yeah, put it in the room on the end.

29:06.621 --> 29:08.223
- I'm staying down there.
- All right.

29:08.323 --> 29:10.058
- All right.
- Is this your room here?

29:10.158 --> 29:12.427
- It's my room.
- It's lovely.

29:12.527 --> 29:14.196
Thank you. It's not clean.

29:14.296 --> 29:16.398
- Okay, now where's the kitchen?
- Let's go that way.

29:16.498 --> 29:18.133
- It's in there. Go ahead.
- I'm comin'.

29:18.233 --> 29:20.101
Don't be pushing on me.

29:20.201 --> 29:22.537
We saw this. This is the
dining room. It's yellow.

29:22.637 --> 29:25.273
It's yellow. It's bright yellow!

29:25.373 --> 29:26.942
It's nice, Mama, huh?

29:27.042 --> 29:29.477
Yeah, it's not my cup
of tea, but you know.

29:29.577 --> 29:31.880
- Back porch and everything.
