43:43.097 --> 43:44.365
What's the problem?

43:44.465 --> 43:46.670
Lacey hadn't told her
mama that we're married.

43:47.268 --> 43:49.370
- What?
- Why ain't you told her?

43:49.470 --> 43:50.638
Well...

43:50.738 --> 43:53.307
my mother had dreams
for my entire life...

43:53.407 --> 43:56.488
and Conner was not in that dream.

43:58.879 --> 44:00.347
I'm sorry. I do...

44:00.447 --> 44:03.417
- I don't understand.
- I think I do. Let me ask you something.

44:03.517 --> 44:06.791
When she had them dreams,
was they in color or black-and-white?

44:11.192 --> 44:13.329
She doesn't want you
with a white man.

44:15.996 --> 44:18.332
I'm sorry. That's awful.

44:18.432 --> 44:20.401
Honey, we taught
all of our children...

44:20.501 --> 44:22.670
"Never see color. Only see heart."

44:22.770 --> 44:26.073
- Isn't that right, Conner?
- That's right.

44:26.173 --> 44:29.777
It's such a shame she does not
know what kind of person you are.

44:30.611 --> 44:32.379
I'll tell you who he is.

44:32.479 --> 44:34.949
Always taught him to
look at a woman's heart.

44:35.049 --> 44:37.118
'Cause that's where their rack hangs.

44:37.218 --> 44:38.385
Daddy.

44:38.485 --> 44:40.621
I'm just kiddin'.
She got a nice rack.

44:40.721 --> 44:42.456
Your mama used to have a nice rack.

44:42.556 --> 44:45.659
Now she bends over, just looks
like she's got a 7-10 split.

44:45.759 --> 44:48.195
- What the hell does that mean?
- It's a bowling term.

44:48.295 --> 44:50.498
- I don't like that, Daddy.
- I don't either.

44:50.598 --> 44:53.934
I'm just kiddin'. I still like to go to
the bowling alley every now and then.

44:54.034 --> 44:56.170
- You're sexy to me.
- Will you hush?

44:56.270 --> 44:58.973
I'm gonna start talking about
all your wrinkly, saggy parts.

44:59.073 --> 45:02.211
- It's like a turkey giblet in there.
- That was over the line.

45:03.711 --> 45:06.883
Well, honey, Conner,
who does she think you are?

45:07.481 --> 45:09.219
She thinks I'm the farm help.

45:10.150 --> 45:12.787
- Well, there's a switcheroo.
- The farm help.

45:12.887 --> 45:15.456
Do you think we should leave?
I think we should maybe leave.

45:15.556 --> 45:18.359
I ain't goin' nowhere.
Hell, I just drove up here.

45:18.459 --> 45:21.395
- I am tired. I want a beer.
- I don't want you guys to leave.

45:21.495 --> 45:23.939
Well, what should we do?

45:25.165 --> 45:27.201
Can you give me
some time to tell her?

45:27.301 --> 45:31.105
I mean, I have to break it to
her gently. She's been very sick.

45:31.205 --> 45:33.407
- Oh, no.
- I'm so sorry.

45:33.507 --> 45:35.910
- What's wrong?
- She has a weak heart.

45:36.010 --> 45:38.145
Then by all means, you just...

45:38.245 --> 45:40.481
take your time and tell
her when you're ready.

45:40.581 --> 45:42.416
- Thank you.
- Okay.

45:42.516 --> 45:45.219
We don't want her ticker
to tock out on you here.

45:45.319 --> 45:47.087
- We'll behave ourselves.
- Yeah.

45:47.187 --> 45:48.923
- You know what we'll be?
- What?

45:49.023 --> 45:51.525
- Parents of the help.
- That's right. Parents of the help.

45:51.625 --> 45:54.562
- "Can I get you something?"
- Let's head in.

45:54.662 --> 45:56.964
- Come on.
- Daddy, behave.

45:57.064 --> 45:59.867
I'll behave. Like a bull in a rodeo.

45:59.967 --> 46:02.670
- Did you paint this? This is fabulous.
- I started.

46:02.770 --> 46:04.672
- Still needs some work.
- Where you at?

46:04.772 --> 46:06.774
I bet this house run them
in the double figures.

46:06.874 --> 46:08.242
- Hey, Madea.
- Hey!

46:08.342 --> 46:10.344
- This is my mama, Kim.
- How you doin'?

46:10.444 --> 46:12.346
- Good to meet you.
- Nice to meet you, Medium.

46:12.446 --> 46:14.281
And this is my daddy, Buddy.

46:14.381 --> 46:16.083
- Nice to meet you.
- How you doin', Buddy?

46:16.183 --> 46:18.552
- I'm doing well.
- I see y'all brought a bag.

46:18.652 --> 46:20.231
No, that's just my wife.

46:20.988 --> 46:24.358
Forgive my husband. He is
just a horse's ass and a half.

46:24.458 --> 46:27.361
- Wait. I smell cookin'.
- Yeah, that's Eileen.

46:27.461 --> 46:29.496
- Her mama was up in there cooking.
- Where is she?

46:29.596 --> 46:31.799
She was in the kitchen,
but she went to the backyard.

46:31.899 --> 46:33.734
Come on. Sit down. Take a load off.

46:33.834 --> 46:36.470
Take a load off. Y'all sit a spell.

46:36.570 --> 46:39.640
- Y'all want something to drink?
- I believe I'll have something.

46:39.740 --> 46:41.642
I like you. You're a nice lady.

46:41.742 --> 46:43.711
Don't be flirting with me
in front of your wife.

46:43.811 --> 46:46.585
If I put this thing on,
you won't be able to get rid of it.

46:47.514 --> 46:49.884
I'll have him pay my rent,
car note and everything else.

46:49.984 --> 46:51.654
I'm from the old school.

46:52.586 --> 46:54.388
Believe me, he can't help it.

46:54.488 --> 46:56.991
And if you can stand him,
you're welcome to him, right?

46:57.091 --> 46:59.360
- Hey, Conner, get me a beer.
- Yes, sir.

46:59.460 --> 47:00.928
Well, Miss Madea...

47:01.028 --> 47:03.998
looks like we're gonna be spending
Christmas dinner together this year...

47:04.098 --> 47:05.566
but don't you worry.

47:05.666 --> 47:07.837
We could care less you're black.

47:10.037 --> 47:12.072
"African-American," Buddy.

47:12.172 --> 47:15.075
Right, whatever. African-American.

47:15.175 --> 47:17.478
That's all right. I don't care
that y'all are white America...

47:17.578 --> 47:19.914
Angro... Angrola-Saxons...
Saxophonists.

47:20.014 --> 47:23.254
I don't care. That don't matter at
all that y'all Anglo-Saxophonists.

47:24.018 --> 47:25.519
I like her.

47:25.619 --> 47:28.055
She's got a good sense of humor
and those big, sturdy feet.

47:28.155 --> 47:31.392
You need a good sense of
humor with this group in here.

47:31.492 --> 47:33.961
- Here, Daddy, beer. Drink up.
- Appreciate it.

47:34.061 --> 47:37.231
- Please, drink up.
- I'll tell you what, Son.

47:37.331 --> 47:39.667
That last girl you with
was so dadgum ugly...

47:39.767 --> 47:41.869
my dog humped her leg
and shut his eyeballs.

47:41.969 --> 47:44.709
Oh, stop it. He's awful!

47:45.706 --> 47:49.576
"He shut his eyeballs." That's ugly.

47:49.676 --> 47:53.280
Please forgive my husband.
He is a wannabe comedian.

47:53.380 --> 47:54.848
You are no Jeff Foxworthy.

47:54.948 --> 47:57.484
Well, I try to be,
but who can? Who can?

47:57.584 --> 48:00.754
Did you hear the one about the
two rabbis and the black dude?

48:00.854 --> 48:02.589
- Daddy.
- No.

48:02.689 --> 48:05.159
Did you hear the one about the
stray bullet that killed the redneck...

48:05.259 --> 48:07.461
for telling the story about the
rabbis and the black dude?

48:07.561 --> 48:09.140
It's hilarious!

48:10.531 --> 48:12.800
I got him, didn't I? I got him.

48:12.900 --> 48:15.844
- Y'all get your ass shot.
- I like her. I do.

48:16.837 --> 48:19.042
I do too. She likes to hang.

48:20.641 --> 48:22.609
No, ain't gonna be no
hanging around here now.

48:22.709 --> 48:24.745
No, he didn't mean that.
He meant that...

48:24.845 --> 48:27.548
You calm the hell down?
You are so politically correct.

48:27.648 --> 48:29.450
They're having fun.
I'm having fun too.

48:29.550 --> 48:31.926
I wasn't offended.
Hell, I got a pistol.

48:32.853 --> 48:35.189
I knew she knew that.
Let me ask you this.

48:35.289 --> 48:36.757
Do you know Oprah?

48:36.857 --> 48:38.659
Honey, I told you...

48:38.759 --> 48:41.161
all black folk don't
necessarily know each other.

48:41.261 --> 48:46.300
- Could've fooled me.
- Do I look like Paul Bunyan or what?

48:46.400 --> 48:50.414
Actually, you sure in the hell do.
And the Jolly Green Giant too. Ho-ho-ho.

48:51.071 --> 48:53.741
- Farmhand, please help me.
- His name is Conner.

48:53.841 --> 48:54.875
Whew!

48:54.975 --> 48:57.011
I think the tree...

48:57.111 --> 48:59.079
would look good right here.

48:59.179 --> 49:01.348
If you don't mind me butting in...

49:01.448 --> 49:04.785
I think it would look really
pretty right here by the window...

49:04.885 --> 49:07.554
and that way all the
passersby can enjoy it.

49:07.654 --> 49:10.224
That's where we had it every year.

49:10.324 --> 49:12.793
- And who are you?
- That's a pretty tree.

49:12.893 --> 49:15.062
I am... I'm Conner's mom.

49:15.162 --> 49:18.641
That's Kim and that's Buddy.
These are Coroner's parents.

49:19.700 --> 49:22.903
This is Eileen. I wanna scream.
I mean, Eileen.

49:23.003 --> 49:27.975
Trees are for the family,
not for strangers.

49:28.075 --> 49:30.077
What the hell these
people doing here?

49:30.177 --> 49:33.258
Mama, they came to visit
Conner for Christmas.

49:34.381 --> 49:39.353
Really? That is just
like my daughter.

49:39.453 --> 49:41.055
I raised you right.

49:41.155 --> 49:45.592
My daughter has always been
good with helping the help.

49:45.692 --> 49:47.728
Yes.

49:47.828 --> 49:50.531
- Where you staying?
- We're thinking of staying here.

49:50.631 --> 49:53.267
Yeah. We drove all the
way up from Louisiana...

49:53.367 --> 49:56.004
to spend Christmas
with Conner and Lacey.

49:57.004 --> 49:59.914
It'll be a little cramped...

50:00.674 --> 50:02.412
but we'll make do.

50:04.311 --> 50:07.081
Madea and I will share a room.

50:07.181 --> 50:09.383
You, Buddy and...

50:09.483 --> 50:10.551
Kim.

50:10.651 --> 50:12.920
Kim, take another room...

50:13.020 --> 50:14.855
- and Carver...
- Conner.

50:14.955 --> 50:16.256
- That's what I said.
- Conner.

50:16.356 --> 50:18.868
Yes, Carver, you can take the sofa.

50:19.960 --> 50:22.329
Let me get some decorations.

50:22.429 --> 50:24.932
Okay. I just...

50:25.032 --> 50:28.402
So many memories just coming
back to me bein' here.

50:28.502 --> 50:32.473
To tell you, Lacey, my mama,
she loved this place. She did.

50:32.573 --> 50:35.542
I'm so happy you all came
back here to take care of it.

50:35.642 --> 50:37.050
Welcome.

50:37.978 --> 50:40.114
Well, my daughter's
paying the mortgage...

50:40.214 --> 50:42.449
so I hope you bring
in a crop this year.

50:42.549 --> 50:44.952
I told you not to buy this farm.

50:45.052 --> 50:48.989
That dam up north caused a lot of
problems this year for the farmers.

50:49.089 --> 50:52.693
But Conner, he's got him a new
strain of corn that takes less water.

50:52.793 --> 50:54.428
Now, how's that work, Conner?

50:54.528 --> 50:57.998
I studied agriculture
at New York State.

50:58.098 --> 50:59.633
Is that where you two met?

50:59.733 --> 51:01.368
Yeah. He's brilliant.

51:01.468 --> 51:04.271
Gets it from his old man.
Runs in the genes.

51:04.371 --> 51:07.641
At the science of it,
not so much the farming.

51:07.741 --> 51:11.011
So genius, little Einstein,
little Stephen Hawkins.

51:11.111 --> 51:14.114
We used to call him
"Smarty Britches" when he was little.

51:14.214 --> 51:17.951
If you put some Viagra in that
tree's water, it'll stay up all year.

51:18.051 --> 51:21.860
You better put some Viagra in your water.
See what happen with your tree.

51:25.192 --> 51:28.529
- All right, let's decorate.
- No, thank you. I can manage.

51:28.629 --> 51:31.431
I brought some decorations
from Atlanta...

51:31.531 --> 51:33.867
and I work at one of the
finest department stores...

51:33.967 --> 51:36.203
so I know a thing or two about taste.

51:36.303 --> 51:37.882
Where...

51:38.305 --> 51:40.274
Where did you get this tree?

51:40.374 --> 51:42.509
I mean, you have a beautiful
Christmas tree...

51:42.609 --> 51:46.122
right outside the kitchen
window and none in the house.

51:48.315 --> 51:49.894
What's wrong?

51:50.484 --> 51:52.553
Please don't tell me that's
your granddaddy's tree.

51:52.653 --> 51:54.154
Oh, dear God.

51:54.254 --> 51:57.324
Mama, was there a yellow ribbon
wrapped around that tree?

51:57.424 --> 51:59.265
Yes, and I cut it off.

52:00.761 --> 52:03.130
Excuse me. Excuse me.

52:03.230 --> 52:04.934
What happened? What?

52:05.932 --> 52:07.968
My mama planted that tree...

52:08.068 --> 52:10.546
in memory of my granddaddy.

52:14.641 --> 52:16.843
Well, how was I
supposed to know that?

52:16.943 --> 52:18.679
This doesn't make any sense. Lacey.

52:18.779 --> 52:22.716
Did these people come
when you bought this land?

52:22.816 --> 52:26.693
This is your land now.
You can do what you want to with it.

52:27.354 --> 52:29.089
Excuse me.

52:29.189 --> 52:30.657
You don't look so good.

52:30.757 --> 52:32.993
Feeling a little light-headed.

52:33.093 --> 52:34.995
Well, sit down then. Sit down.

52:35.095 --> 52:36.503
Okay.

52:38.332 --> 52:41.068
It's all these strange people
in this house, that's what it is.

52:41.168 --> 52:43.270
It ain't them people,
it's you! Hell, you!

52:43.370 --> 52:46.440
You lost your damn mind.
You done lost your damn mind!

52:46.540 --> 52:50.210
Anytime you see somebody with a
yellow ribbon on the tree, Eileen...

52:50.310 --> 52:52.946
a yellow ribbon,
that means a memoriam.

52:53.046 --> 52:54.248
Don't you know what that means?

52:54.348 --> 52:56.717
Everybody in the USA knows
what a memoriam is...

52:56.817 --> 52:58.819
when you see a yellow
ribbon on a damn tree.

52:58.919 --> 53:00.487
You work on my nerves.

53:00.587 --> 53:03.890
That poor woman is probably crying
'cause you cut down her daddy's tree.

53:03.990 --> 53:05.959
What wrong with you,
cutting down her daddy's tree?

53:06.059 --> 53:08.128
You know what's gonna happen?
I'm gonna make this plain.

53:08.228 --> 53:10.130
You're gonna go to bed,
slip into a coma...

53:10.230 --> 53:11.965
and everybody gonna wonder
what happened to you.

53:12.065 --> 53:14.635
I did it. It's Christmas, damn it!

53:14.735 --> 53:17.671
I don't know, Buddy.
I don't think I can deal with this.

53:17.771 --> 53:20.107
I don't like it. It's wrong.

53:20.207 --> 53:24.211
I can't pretend to be somebody.
I'm not an actress. I'm not Reba.

53:24.311 --> 53:27.080
Maybe we should just leave.
Let's pack up and leave tomorrow.

53:27.180 --> 53:29.082
No, we're not going back home.
We're staying here.

53:29.182 --> 53:30.751
- It's Christmas.
- And that woman...

53:30.851 --> 53:34.655
she cuts down my daddy's memory tree
and acts like she doesn't even care!

53:34.755 --> 53:36.723
Honey, I know. It stinks. I get it.

53:36.823 --> 53:38.792
You know what?
We'll get you another tree.

53:38.892 --> 53:41.928
I want that tree. I want my
daddy's tree. What about our son?

53:42.028 --> 53:44.598
Conner just stands there and doesn't
say anything back to this woman.

53:44.698 --> 53:47.668
He's just pretending,
just saying nothin' to this woman.

53:47.768 --> 53:51.538
Sweetheart, you know our kid.
He can't tell no to anybody.

53:51.638 --> 53:53.106
Let him figure it out.

53:53.206 --> 53:54.941
- You want some of this?
- No, not now.

53:55.041 --> 53:58.178
- You know you want some of this.
- I don't. It's too much for me.

53:58.278 --> 54:00.180
Remember that game we
played when we was kids?

54:00.280 --> 54:02.249
- Mystery Date?
- No, the Ghost and the Damsel.

54:02.349 --> 54:04.318
- You remember that?
- Buddy Williams...

54:04.418 --> 54:07.454
We are not playing... This is not the
time or the place. Don't you dare.

54:07.554 --> 54:09.823
Go take a cold shower
and get off of me.

54:09.923 --> 54:11.792
Go throw some milk on that thing.

54:11.892 --> 54:14.472
I think I left my bag in...

54:15.429 --> 54:17.509
one of my bags here.

54:23.003 --> 54:24.938
- You think she noticed me?
- Yes!

54:25.038 --> 54:27.675
- Yes!
- Oh, damn.

54:30.477 --> 54:33.880
How to stop diabetes before it starts.
That's what AARP talking about.

54:33.980 --> 54:36.060
You got to read this,
this is pretty good.

54:47.881 --> 54:49.483
- Hi.
- Hey.

54:50.083 --> 54:51.821
Heard about the sponsorship?

54:52.586 --> 54:54.555
Yeah, just found out about it.

54:54.655 --> 54:57.124
- We got a problem.
- What's that?

54:57.224 --> 54:59.463
Sponsor is Sheldon Construction.

55:02.930 --> 55:05.666
Same Sheldon Construction that built
the dam that put us all out of business?

55:05.766 --> 55:09.177
- That's the one.
- Hell no. You see?

55:10.270 --> 55:11.849
Unbelievable.

55:16.892 --> 55:18.361
Eileen, what you doin'?

55:18.461 --> 55:19.962
I knew it.

55:20.062 --> 55:22.231
He's in the Ku Klux Klan.

55:22.331 --> 55:23.910
What?

55:24.400 --> 55:28.003
He was wearing the sheet
when I went in the room.

55:28.103 --> 55:30.039
Them people are not
in no Ku Klux Klan.

55:30.139 --> 55:31.907
I saw the Klan today.
That ain't the Klan.

55:32.007 --> 55:35.511
- They probably trying to make up the bed.
- I know the Klan when I see it.

55:35.611 --> 55:37.980
There you go, overreacting,
like you always do.

55:38.080 --> 55:40.558
- Yes, he is.
- Always jump to conclusions.

55:41.317 --> 55:42.718
Stop jumping to conclusions.

55:42.818 --> 55:45.228
No, baby. No.

55:45.821 --> 55:47.289
I know what I saw.

55:47.389 --> 55:49.425
Eileen, you gonna
get your pressure up.

55:49.525 --> 55:54.063
I'm gonna sleep with
one eye open tonight.

55:54.163 --> 55:58.401
Yes. Oh, Lord, my poor daughter,
she's so naive.

55:58.501 --> 56:01.270
She don't know what's going on.
She don't have a clue.

56:01.370 --> 56:04.173
You don't have a clue, talkin'
about sleeping with one eye open.

56:04.273 --> 56:06.942
I hope it's not the lazy one,
'cause that one always look closed.

56:07.042 --> 56:08.844
Them people are not in the Klan.

56:08.944 --> 56:11.113
You put all of this stuff
in front of that door.

56:11.213 --> 56:12.848
All that stuff in
front the damn door.

56:12.948 --> 56:16.185
I go to the bathroom, four, five, six,
seven, eight, nine, 10, 12 times a night...

56:16.285 --> 56:18.187
and if I laugh too hard,
I squirt pee.

56:18.287 --> 56:19.989
You got to move that stuff.

56:20.089 --> 56:23.466
How can I go to the bathroom at
night with all that in front the door?

56:26.295 --> 56:27.997
What this?

56:28.097 --> 56:30.871
- I can't sit on this cup!
- Then stand up.

57:09.805 --> 57:11.273
Conner, I'm sorry.

57:11.373 --> 57:13.919
- Can I ask you something?
- What's that?

57:16.011 --> 57:18.581
- Are you ashamed of me?
- No.

57:18.681 --> 57:20.816
Then why won't you tell her?

57:20.916 --> 57:24.987
I've never let my mother
down my entire life. Okay?

57:25.087 --> 57:28.991
I've done everything
she wanted. Always.

57:29.091 --> 57:32.035
And this is the first time I've
done something that I want.

57:33.562 --> 57:35.631
Conner, it's gonna break her heart.

57:35.731 --> 57:37.199
You gotta understand that.

57:37.299 --> 57:39.802
You have to understand
how this makes me feel.

57:39.902 --> 57:43.381
I love you. I'm proud of us.
I don't care who knows.

57:47.543 --> 57:50.715
- Are you coming to bed?
- You mean the sofa, right?

57:51.313 --> 57:53.716
You know the walls are thin.

57:53.816 --> 57:56.021
My patience is getting
there with this.

58:04.927 --> 58:07.863
And I told her, "You better
get the hell on out the way."

58:07.963 --> 58:10.232
Lord, that was funny.
Your mama was something else.

58:10.332 --> 58:12.070
Here you are, Miss Murphy.

58:13.435 --> 58:15.638
Three little eggs.

58:15.738 --> 58:17.545
Mama, it's fine.

58:18.474 --> 58:20.175
Would you like some coffee, Conner?

58:20.275 --> 58:23.322
No, I gotta tend to the animals.

